    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1189"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1189">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/38.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>251. My despatch 43 and your 1605 of November 21. The provisional government has
                    issued decree extending time for revalidation of mining titles to March 31 next
                    but leaving standing the regulations and penalties in circular with my number 43
                    of September 29. I consider it necessary to make the Government realize the
                    trouble, difficulty and expense which such procedure will cause to the entire
                    mining community and have already taken this up with president Guiterrez.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
